   Bob Lynn's Wild Rice Salad


   From ``Comfortable Entertaining'' by Nathalie Dupree (Viking,
$29.95). This is an excellent dish for Thanksgiving, a fall dinner
party or buffet. (Bob Lynn develops recipes for the Houston's
restaurant chain.)


   Ingredients: &QL; 
4 cups water or chicken stock &QL; 
1 cup wild rice, rinsed thoroughly under running water &QL; 
\ cup chopped dried figs or cherries &QL; 
 &QL;


   Dressing (recipe follows) &QL; 
{ cup each, toasted: pecans and cashews, chopped into \-inch
pieces &QL; 
 &QL; 
2 tablespoons each, finely chopped: celery and red onion &QL; 
\ cup finely chopped green onion, green part only &QL; 
1 bunch arugula or watercress (optional) &QL; 
 &QL;


   Bring water to a boil in a large, heavy saucepan. Add rice,
cover and cook until the grains split, 50 to 60 minutes. Place figs
in { cup hot water to plump them. After 30 minutes, drain; discard
water.


   Make Dressing. In a large bowl, toss rice, pecans, cashews,
celery, red onion, green onion and figs. Pour enough Dressing over
rice to coat. Toss with arugula. Serve warm or at room temperature.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.


   Variation: For a more festive appearance, add 1 or 2 cups orange
sections or peeled orange slices.


   &QL;


   Dressing &QL;


   Ingredients: &QL; 
2 tablespoons red wine vinegar &QL; 
1 tablespoon fresh lemon juice &QL; 
2 garlic cloves, finely chopped &QL; 
1 teaspoon each: Dijon mustard and sugar &QL; 
 &QL; 
Salt and freshly ground black pepper &QL; 
{ cup vegetable oil &QL; 
\ cup olive oil &QL; 
 &QL;


   In a blender or food processor, combine vinegar, lemon juice,
garlic, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper. Process until smooth, then
slowly add oils until emulsified. Dressing can be made in advance
and refrigerated.


